This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the expressiveness of deep models and their optimization. The paper also explores the connection between neural networks and kernel learning, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 

The paper also touches upon the optimization process, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

The use of neural networks in computer vision is a popular area of research, and since the paper explores the properties of neural networks, it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The paper's focus on the theoretical understanding behind neural network learning suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper's exploration of the neural spectrum and its behavior with different learning rates suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
